Custom trap classes
===================

This directory contains concrete implementations of optical trap types,
each subclassing ``QFab.lib.traps.QTrap``.

Built-in trap types
-------------------

| Class         | Description                                              |
|---------------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| QTweezer      | Single Gaussian focus                                    |
| QVortex       | Laguerre-Gaussian vortex beam with topological charge    |
| QRingTrap     | Annular optical trap                                     |
| QTrapArray    | Rectangular grid with optional mask and position jitter  |
| QLetterArray  | Single dot-matrix character (A-Z, a-z, 0-9) as tweezers |
| QTextArray    | String of QLetterArray characters                        |

Writing a custom trap
---------------------

1. Subclass ``QFab.lib.traps.QTrap`` (for a single trap) or
   ``QFab.lib.traps.QTrapGroup`` (for a composite).
2. Implement ``__init__``, calling ``super().__init__(*args, **kwargs)``.
3. Override ``_draw(self, field)`` to add your contribution to the
   complex field array.
4. Call ``self.registerProperty(name, ...)`` for each user-adjustable
   parameter you want exposed in the Traps tab.
5. Add your class to ``__init__.py`` and ``__all__`` so it appears in
   the Add Trap menu.

See ``QTweezer.py`` for the simplest possible example, and
``QTrapArray.py`` for an example with registered properties and
child-management signals (``reshaping`` / ``reshaped``).
